[{"id":"VR116775","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR116772.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following statements did most poll respondents say described the state of political affairs in Nigeria?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR116775_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a chart with four bars of data titled “Nigerians Have Doubts About Their Political System. How well does the statement describe Nigeria?” Each bar of data has two categories: not well and well. The data represented in the chart are as follows. Box 1. Elected officials care what ordinary people think: Not well, 59 percent; Well, 38 percent. Box 2. The court system treats everyone fairly: Not well, 54 percent; Well, 43 percent. Box 3. No matter who wins an election, things do not much change very much: Not well, 41 percent; Well, 57 percent. Box 4. Most politicians are corrupt: Not well, 27 percent; Well, 72 percent.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR116772.g07.png\"/></div></div>"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Elected officials care what ordinary people think.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">No matter who wins an election, things do not change very much.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The court systems treat everyone fairly.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Most politicians are corrupt.</p>"],"answer":3}]